name: Wood Sandpiper
description: Medium-sized brownish wader with a white belly, varied pale spotting and spangling on back

name: Rock Pigeon
description: Pale gray overall with two bold black wingbars and iridescent purple and green on neck

name: Alexandrine Parakeet

name: Grey Heron
description: Generally quite common and conspicuous in wetland habitats from marshes

name: White Wagtail
description: Distinctive but variable: all plumages are some bold combination of black, white, and gray

name: Indian Paradise-Flycatcher
description: A graceful looking flycatcher, the adult male sport a long ribbonlike tail.

name: American Kestrel
description: In flight, note long, narrow wings and square-tipped tail.
